<?xml version="1.1" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<slideshow>
	<documentinfo>
		<author>Jim Dee</author>
		<version>1.1</version>
    <title>Chicken Stock</title>
		<comment>This is a basic, white chicken stock. It is light and neutral in flavour, and therefore serves as an excellent, all-purpose stock. Please see the de-boning video for instructions on preparing the chicken carcass. 
		</comment>
		<cook>1 day</cook>
		<prep>10 min</prep>
		<price>Â£3</price>
		<veg>No</veg>
		<width>1440</width>
		<height>900</height>
	</documentinfo>
	<defaults>
		<backgroundcolor>#FFFFFF</backgroundcolor>
		<font>Helvetica Neue Thin</font>
		<fontsize>24</fontsize>
		<linecolor>#000000</linecolor>
		<fontcolor>#000000</fontcolor>
		<fillcolor>#CCCCCC</fillcolor>
	</defaults>
	<ingredients>
		<ingredient name="chicken carcass" amount="1" units="" />
		<ingredient name="carrot" amount="1" units="whole" />
		<ingredient name="onions" amount="2" units="whole" />
		<ingredient name="leek" amount="1" units="whole" />
		<ingredient name="bay leaves" amount="3" units="leaves" />
		<ingredient name="thyme" amount="3" units="sprigs" />
		<ingredient name="black peppercorns" amount="6" units="whole" />
	</ingredients>

	<slide id="0" duration="20" lastSlide="false">
		<text xstart="10" ystart="10" xend="1000" yend="300" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="40" fontcolor="#000000" orientation="0"> 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="true" italic="false">
        		<textstring>Chicken Stock</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>
		<text xstart="15" ystart="70" xend="1200" yend="300" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" orientation="0"> 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="false" italic="false" branch="10">
        		<textstring>I usually buy my chicken whole, and prepare the carcass myself. A whole chicken usually costs about as much as 2 chicken breasts, so it is far more economical to buy a whole bird. </textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>
		
		<image urlname="file:../Resources/Butternut_Squash/IMG_butnut_0.jpg" xstart="250" ystart="200" width="800" height="533" layer="1" />		
		<image urlname="file:../Resources/background.png" xstart="0" ystart="0" width="1440" height="900" layer="0" />		
	</slide>

	<slide id="1" duration="30" lastSlide="false">
		<text xstart="10" ystart="10" xend="1000" yend="300" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="40" fontcolor="#000000" orientation="0"> 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="true" italic="false">
        		<textstring>Step One</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>
		<text xstart="15" ystart="70" xend="1200" yend="200" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" orientation="0"> 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="false" italic="false">
        		<textstring>Chop the carcass into 1-2 inch pieces, along with the wings and the trim from the legs. Discard any small organs remaining on the bird, and wash off as much blood as possible.   </textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>  
		<text xstart="150" ystart="550" xend="1000" yend="475" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" orientation="0"> 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="false" italic="false">
        		<textstring>Put the chicken a large saucepan, cover with water, and place on a medium low heat. Bring very slowly to the boil, skimming off anything which rises to the top. </textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>     		
        		
		<image urlname="file:../Resources/Butternut_Squash/IMG_butnut_1.jpg" xstart="100" ystart="200" width="475" height="316" layer="2" />	
		<image urlname="file:../Resources/Butternut_Squash/IMG_butnut_2.jpg" xstart="650" ystart="200" width="475" height="316" layer="2" />		
			
		<image urlname="file:../Resources/background.png" xstart="0" ystart="0" width="1440" height="900" layer="0" />
	</slide>

	<slide id="2" duration="30" lastSlide="false">
		<text xstart="10" ystart="10" xend="1000" yend="300" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="40" fontcolor="#000000" > 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="true" italic="false">
        		<textstring>Step Two</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>
		<text xstart="15" ystart="70" xend="1400" yend="600" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" > 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="false" italic="false">
        		<textstring>Just before the water comes to the boil, turn off the heat and pour away the water. Rinse the chicken bones while they are still hot to remove any scum. Clean the pan as well. This blanching process enables a clearer stock. Put the chicken back in the pan, and place on a low heat. Bring to a simmer and skim frequently.   </textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>     
		<text xstart="15" ystart="600" xend="1000" yend="800" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" > 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="false" italic="false">
				<textstring>Simmer for 1 hour, and then add all the other ingredients. Simmer for a further hour and a half then strain the stock into another saucepan.   </textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>		
        		
		<image urlname="file:../Resources/Butternut_Squash/IMG_butnut_4.jpg" xstart="15" ystart="175" width="600" height="400" layer="2" />	
		<image urlname="file:../Resources/Butternut_Squash/IMG_butnut_5.jpg" xstart="650" ystart="175" width="600" height="400" layer="2" />		
		<image urlname="file:../Resources/background.png" xstart="0" ystart="0" width="1440" height="900" layer="0" />
	</slide>

	<slide id="3" duration="30" lastSlide="false">
		<text xstart="10" ystart="10" xend="1000" yend="300" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="40" fontcolor="#000000" > 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="true" italic="false">
        		<textstring>Step Three</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>
		<text xstart="15" ystart="70" xend="650" yend="400" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" >
			<textbody >
        		<textstring>Discard the solids. Reduce the stock over a high heat until reduced by one third. Chill, and remove the fat from the top.  </textstring>
      			</textbody>
        </text>
        
        
		<image urlname="file:../Resources/Butternut_Squash/IMG_butnut_6.jpg" xstart="650" ystart="70" width="600" height="400" layer="3" />
		<image urlname="file:../Resources/Butternut_Squash/IMG_butnut_7.jpg" xstart="15" ystart="360" width="600" height="400" layer="3" />
		<image urlname="file:../Resources/background.png" xstart="0" ystart="0" width="1440" height="900" layer="0" />
					
	</slide>

	
	<slide id="4" duration="30" lastSlide="true">
		<text xstart="10" ystart="10" xend="1000" yend="300" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="40" fontcolor="#000000" > 
			<textbody underlined="false" bold="true" italic="false">
        		<textstring>Done.</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text>
		<text xstart="100" ystart="650" xend="1200" yend="300" font="Helvetica Neue Thin" fontsize="30" fontcolor="#000000" orientation="0">
			<textbody >
        		<textstring>A dark chicken stock can be made in a similar way as above, but by replacing the blanching with oven roasting. Toss the bones in a little vegetable oil and roast at gas mark 7 for 30-45 minutes until golden brown. Lightly brown the vegetables in a frying pan. Add everything to a large pan, cover with cold water and bring to a simmer. Simmer for 4 hours then strain as above.</textstring>
      			</textbody>
		</text> 
		<image urlname="file:../Resources/Butternut_Squash/IMG_butnut_13.jpg" xstart="200" ystart="70" width="850" height="566" layer="7" />			
		<image urlname="file:../Resources/background.png" xstart="0" ystart="0" width="1440" height="900" layer="0" />
	</slide>

</slideshow>